Operators:
Operators are used to perform operations on variables and values.These are kind of special symbols.

Operands: The values or variables that an operator acts on are called operands.
Operators: The symbols that represent operations are called operators.

Example:
X + Y
Here, + is the operator.
X and Y are operands.3

Python divides the operators in the following groups:

•	Arithmetic Operators
•	Relational Operators
•	Assignment Operators
•	Logical Operators
•	Identity Operators
•	Membership Operators
•	Bitwise Operators

Discussed Operators:
•	Arithmetic Operators
•	Relational Operators
•	Assignment Operators
•	Logical Operators

Control Statements: Back bone of any programming language. They allows you to control the flow of your program's execution based on specific conditions.

3 Types:

1. Conditional Statements or Decision Making statements
2. Transfer Statements or Jumping Statements
3. Iterative Statements or Looping Statements


Conditional statements gives your program the ability to make decisions and perform different actions based on those decisions.
We use these statements to execute certain piece of code based on wheather a condition is TRUE or FALSE.
1. if
2. elif
3. else
4. nested if
5. shorthand if
6. shorthand if else




